result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and Operating w/ PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC-Passenger < 16 Yrs (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • Brian J. Davidenko was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs w/ Passenger < 16 Yrs Old), an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Fine is paid in full from cash bond previously posted.  The remaining portion of the cash bond has been applied to companion Waushara Co Case No. 2014CF000107.
DNA Surcharge paid in full from cash bond previously posted.
Defendant to obtain a High School Equivalency Diploma (HSED) during the pendency of probation term.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.
